  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed flats, by reason of the insufficient internal floor area to flat 78A and 80A; insufficient ventilation, outlook and access to natural sunlight/daylight to both bedroom of flat 78B and 80B; cramped and contrived living area for flat 78B and 80B; impractical bike store and would not provide an area that is 'fit for purpose'; insufficient provision of refuse storage would cumulatively result in a poor standard of accommodation to the detriment of the amenity of future occupiers of the site.  As such, it is contrary to policy 3.5 of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policies D6, SI8 and T5 of the London Plan (2021) and the National Planning Policy Framework (2023). | The proposed development would result in a net loss of ground floor retail floorspace in a designated Primary Shop Frontage, to the detriment of the retail character and vitality of the parade.  As such, the proposal is contrary with policy 4B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013). | The proposed first floor roof terrace, would give rise to the potential for direct overlooking of the neighbouring property, causing an impact on the residential amenity of no. 76 and 82 Bilton Road by way of overlooking and loss of privacy. As such, the proposal is contrary to policies D4 and D6 of the London Plan (2021), policy 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013), and SPD4."
  ],
